Our Customer Services department is looking for a business analyst to improve its processes and IT solutions in order to increase team efficiency and customer satisfaction. By joining us, you will be a key player in Creaform's growth. Come and take up new challenges and join a passionate and determined team. Choose Creaform!
 You'll be responsible for
 


Reviewing and analyzing the effectiveness and efficiency of our existing processes and their interconnection with other Creaform processes in order to develop improvement strategies

Analyzing user needs and identifying improvement opportunities while taking into account our business constraints and issues;

Ensuring the deployment of system initiatives by defining the use cases;

Defining and contributing to test plans and ensure their implementation with the power users.

Ensuring communication of changes, training plan and content to be deployed by your colleagues, the technical support coordinators;

Ensuring the management of all automations related to the different access profiles;

Ensuring the maximum simplification of operations in relation to the client.


 Your projects will lead you to
 


Collaborate with managers to define the vision and opportunities for the evolution of processes and systems;

Participate in the quality assurance of developed solutions to ensure that features and functions meet requirements;

Collaborate with the IT development team to share the vision, direction and needs of the department and facilitate the processing of bugs and requests for improvements or changes;

Represent the department when new system initiatives are being considered, and contribute to the selection of new software solutions as needed;

Monitor the progress of sprints and projects by participating in various follow-up and start-up meetings with the IT department;

Ensure the maintenance of documentation relevant to the proper functioning of the Client Services teams;

Develop and maintain activity reports and KPIs related to all Customer Service processes as well as customer satisfaction.


 You have the profile we are looking for if you...
 


Have a minimum of 5 years of relevant experience in systems requirements analysis;

Hold a university degree in administration, information systems or other relevant field.

Have demonstrated your ability to prioritize and execute tasks under pressure.

Are detail-oriented and have excellent analytical and problem-solving skills;

Have strong political sense and the ability to argue your ideas;

Enjoy teamwork;

Have excellent project management skills with the ability to manage multiple files simultaneously;

Are fluent in English and French, both written and spoken;

Are at ease in a fast-paced and constantly changing environment;

Are an autonomous, resourceful and proactive person


 You earn points if you...
 


Know a CRM platform such as Salesforce.


 In exchange, we offer you...
 


The chance to work in a stimulating work environment within a human and passionate team, for which pleasure and well-being at work are non-negotiable;

The opportunity to develop your skills and expertise;

The pride of working in a successful technology company, open to the world;

Flexible schedules;

A generous and flexible remote-working policy, even after Covid, when the position allows it;

A salary and growth potential that meets your expectations;

A wide range of social activities, and much more.


 
Consider applying even if your skillset is not a perfect match. We believe our individual background and experiences, paired with passion, can go a long way.

